Twitter users have been reacting to the video documenting instances of #SexForGrades in at least two institutions of higher learning in Nigeria and Ghana. In the documentary, which was shot by the BBC, two lecturers were caught on tape soliciting sex from students in return for favours. Since the documentary was published, Nigerians on social media have been narrating their #SexForGrades experiences at different universities across the nation. READ ALSO: UNILAG lecturer caught in sex-for-grade scandal See reactions:              